{"lemma":"حَدَقاتٌ","slug":"حَدَقاتٌ","root":"ح.د.ق","root_slug":"ح-د-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-د-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7369","n7374"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pupil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare حَدَقَ (ḥadaqa, “to stare at”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.da.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7369","headword_ar":"حَدَقَهُ","root":"Hdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEayonihi","text_ar":"بِعَيْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadoqN","text_ar":"حَدْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked at it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHadaqaniY Alqawomu biA^aboSaArihimo","text_ar":"فَحَدَقَنِى القَوْمُ بِاَبْصَارِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, cast the blacks of their eyes at me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadaqahu","text_ar":"حَدَقَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, hit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt, the black of his eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadaqa","text_ar":"حَدَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwqN","text_ar":"حُدُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of one that is dying ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may~it","text_ar":"مَيِّت"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened his eyes, and moved his eyelids,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twinkled with his eyes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almay~ita yaHodiqu","text_ar":"المَيِّتَ يَحْدِقُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him that was dying open his eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.)       -A3-  See also 4."}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7374","headword_ar":"حَدَقَةٌ","root":"Hdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hunoduwqapu","text_ar":"حُنْدُوقَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinodiyqapN","text_ar":"حِنْدِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but IDrd doubts the correctness of this, (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black of the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, Msb, K;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round part in the middle of the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater black"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eye; (S, TA;) the smaller being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAZir","text_ar":"نَاظِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or pupil], in which is what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnu AlEayoni","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانُ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it is like a mirror, in which one facing it sees his figure; (TA;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, of the eye, that is surrounded by the white;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iris, together with the whole of the anterior chamber of the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is in the middle of the white of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj in his “Khalk el-Insán:”) or, as some say, externally, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black of the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and internally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarazap","text_ar":"خَرَزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lens"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [and sometimes the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"absolutely; as, for instance, in a phrase mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAba","text_ar":"ذَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*wb","text_ar":"ذوب"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaqN","text_ar":"حَدَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K) [or rather this is a coll. gen. n.,] and [the pl. is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAqN","text_ar":"اَحْدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaqaAtN","text_ar":"حَدَقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidaAqN","text_ar":"حِدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) which last is applied by Aboo-Dhu-eyb to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadaqap","text_ar":"حَدَقَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together with what surrounds it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takal~amotu EalaY Hadaqi","text_ar":"تَكَلَّمْتُ عَلَى حَدَقِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomi","text_ar":"القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I spoke while the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, looked at me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumaApu AlHadaqi","text_ar":"رُمَاةُ الحَدَقِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those who hit the mark in throwing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shooting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazaluwA fiY mivoli Hadaqapi AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"نَزَلُوا فِى مِثْلِ حَدَقَةِ البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighted and abode, in a tract abounding with herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdqp","text_ar":"حدقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the camel because this is plentifully supplied with moisture. (TA from a trad.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb"]}]}}